679. Abiisse. The MSS. have abisse, but their spelling in these forms is a very uncertain guide. Thus they offer perissem Aul. 669, uenisse Stich. 232 (uerzz'z'ssc A), perisse Cure. 130, 133, abisse Merc. 223, adisse Aul. 815, redisse Stich. 507 (rediisse A), where the four-syllabled forms are required by the metre. In no line is the three-syllabled form of a Compound of eo with a Preposition required by the metre. (In Alere. 804 read Rus abiisse aibant.)
